idl_bin instructions for developers

Here are the instructions to modify/add arguments to the config file and how
to build the new compiled file (idl_bin.sav)

#1 add the new argument in the idl_bin.cfg file
   If new argument is my_new_file.dat then add the following line above </configuration>
   ex:
	<name_of_new_argument>my_new_file.dat</name_of_new_argument>

#2 add the reading of this new argument in the idl_bin.pro file
   around line 80 (;read config file)
   ex:
	value_of_new_argument = file->getValue(tag=['configuration','name_of_new_argument'])

#3 add the new argument to the procedure call. If the new argument is for example when calling dqtbinning
   add this
   ex:
	dqtbinning, .... , name_of_new_argument=value_of_new_argument

#4 recompile code by changing the default idl and just typing make in the same folder
   > export IDL_DIR='/SNS/software/itt/idl8
   > make

#5 Running idl_bin will use the new .sav file
   > ./idl_bin		








